Title: THE LAST DEPOSIT
Credit: Written by
Author: Test Author
Draft date: May 13, 2026
Contact: test@example.com

====

FADE IN:

INT. DETECTIVE'S APARTMENT - NIGHT

Rain hammers the windows. MAYA, 30s, paces with a glass of bourbon. A laptop glows on the desk. A revolver and a leather briefcase sit beside it.

Her phone buzzes. She grabs it, reads the message, and yanks her coat off the hook.

MAYA
(into phone)
I'm on my way.

She slams the phone down and grabs her keys.

CUT TO:

EXT. WAREHOUSE DISTRICT - CONTINUOUS

A black sedan screeches around the corner. Maya kills the engine and steps out, pistol drawn. A crowd of dockworkers scatters at the sight.

She moves toward the building. A stray dog barks from an alley. Fog drifts across the asphalt.

MAYA
(to herself)
Just like old times.

INT. WAREHOUSE - MOMENTS LATER

VIKTOR, 50s, weathered with a scar across his cheek, sits behind a desk in a tailored suit, smoking a cigar. Two GUARDS flank him, rifles ready. Maya enters, pistol up.

VIKTOR
You came alone? *Foolish.*

MAYA
Where's the package?

VIKTOR
Always so direct.

Suddenly, an EXPLOSION rips through the back wall. Smoke and debris fill the room. Viktor's guards fire wildly. Maya dives behind a crate.

MAYA (CONT'D)
Drop the gun, Viktor!

VIKTOR (V.O.)
You'll never find it.

A second explosion. The ceiling collapses.

EXT. ROOFTOP - DAY

Maya stands at the edge in a white dress, the wind whipping her hair. A helicopter circles overhead. She holds an old photograph in one hand and a lighter in the other.

She sets the photo aflame and watches it burn. The crowd below cheers as fireworks ignite over the city.

MAYA
(quietly)
**Goodbye.**

FADE OUT.

THE END
